        "content": "<p>Hello everyone,<br>\nI'm currently trying to prove that a certain continuous map</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ContinuousMap</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Y</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>is an embedding and I decided to prove it by using embedding_iff and proving that it is both injective and inducing, but I am currently a little stuck when trying to prove that it is inducing. I know how to prove that a set is open in X iff its image is open in Y, but I can't find a lemma in mathlib that shows that a map is inducing if it has this property. </p>\n<p>The only characterizations of inducing maps all yield that f is inducing if and only if </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">TopologicalSpace</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">induced</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">TopologicalSpace</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Y</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>but I don't know how to prove induced f (TopologicalSpace Y) with what I've proven either. I've tried loogle, but I haven't found any lemma that seems useful.<br>\nCould someone please give me a hint on how to prove that f is inducing? I am not looking for code for the lemma I'm looking for, just maybe a hint on how to proceed.</p>",
